.TH INSTALL\-COMPLETIONS 1 "2026-04-04" "machine-setup 2.0" "Machine Setup Manual"
.SH NAME
install\-completions.sh \- install shell completions for setup.sh
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B install\-completions.sh
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Installs shell completion scripts for \fBsetup.sh\fR into the appropriate
system or user directories. Supports bash, zsh, and fish shells. By default,
installs completions for the current shell only; use \fB\-\-all\fR to install
for all supported shells.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-all
Install completions for all supported shells (bash, zsh, fish).
.TP
.B \-\-bash
Install bash completions only.
.TP
.B \-\-zsh
Install zsh completions only.
.TP
.B \-\-fish
Install fish completions only.
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Show what would be installed without writing any files.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show the help message and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Error (unsupported shell, missing completion directory, write failure).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Install completions for the current shell:
.B install\-completions.sh
.TP
Install completions for all shells:
.B install\-completions.sh \-\-all
.TP
Preview zsh completion installation:
.B install\-completions.sh \-\-zsh \-\-dry\-run
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR setup.sh (1)
.SH AUTHORS
Machine Setup contributors.
